    <div class="hospice-text">
        <h3>What’s Covered Under Hospice Care (What Medicare Covers)</h3>

        <p>Before starting hospice care, you are eligible for a consultation with a hospice doctor or the medical director. This discussion is to answer your questions and help you understand your care options.</p>

        <p>We recommend you always ask about the best approach to managing your pain and symptoms under the hospice palliative umbrella—even if you choose not to proceed with hospice care.</p>

        <p>Once hospice begins, Medicare or Medicaid covers all services related to your terminal illness and any associated conditions—as long as care is provided by a Medicare-approved hospice provider.</p>

        <p>Hospice services are typically offered at home but may also be provided at other residences, including inpatient facilities, when needed. Your customized care plan may include:</p>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Section 2: Covered Services List -->
<section class="hospice-box image-right bg-tan" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="900">
    <div class="hospice-img">
        <img src="~/images/hospice_7_2.webp" alt="Medicare consultation" />
    </div>
